text: Holliday Clark Grainger (born 27 March 1988) is an English actress. Her TV roles include Lucrezia Borgia in the Showtime series The Borgias (2011–2013), Bonnie Parker in Bonnie & Clyde (2013), Robin Ellacott in Strike (2017–present) and DI Rachel Carey in The Capture (2019). Her movie roles include Great Expectations (2012), Cinderella (2015), The Finest Hours (2016) and Tulip Fever (2017). Grainger was born in Didsbury, Manchester.
